{"paragraphs":[{"text":"%md\r\n# Spotify Music Big Data Cleaning and Multi-Dimensional Analysis Report Based on Hive SQL\r\n### Course Name: STQD6324 Data Management\r\n### Student ID: P165401 \r\n### Experimental Environment: Apache Hadoop / Apache Hive / Apache Zeppelin\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## 1. Experimental Background and Data Preparation\r\nThe objective of this experiment is to leverage a distributed computing platform to preprocess a massive dataset of Spotify music attributes. The raw dataset encompasses core track characteristics (such as artist, track name, genre, and release date) along with digital audio metrics. Prior to data analytics, critical data quality issues within the raw dataset—including **malformed string encodings, missing field values, and structural column misalignments**—must be systematically resolved via ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) pipelines.","user":"anonymous","dateUpdated":"2026-06-24T13:37:43+0000","config":{"colWidth":12,"enabled":true,"results":{},"editorSetting":{"language":"markdown","editOnDblClick":true},"editorMode":"ace/mode/markdown","editorHide":true,"tableHide":false},"settings":{"params":{},"forms":{}},"results":{"code":"SUCCESS","msg":[{"type":"HTML","data":"<h1>Spotify Music Big Data Cleaning and Multi-Dimensional Analysis Report Based on Hive SQL</h1>\n<h3>Course Name: STQD6324 Data Management</h3>\n<h3>Student ID: P165401</h3>\n<h3>Experimental Environment: Apache Hadoop / Apache Hive / Apache Zeppelin</h3>\n<hr />\n<h2>1. Experimental Background and Data Preparation</h2>\n<p>The objective of this experiment is to leverage a distributed computing platform to preprocess a massive dataset of Spotify music attributes. The raw dataset encompasses core track characteristics (such as artist, track name, genre, and release date) along with digital audio metrics. Prior to data analytics, critical data quality issues within the raw dataset—including <strong>malformed string encodings, missing field values, and structural column misalignments</strong>—must be systematically resolved via ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) pipelines.</p>\n"}]},"apps":[],"jobName":"paragraph_1782301483931_-1329259102","id":"20260624-114443_1501410035","dateCreated":"2026-06-24T11:44:43+0000","dateStarted":"2026-06-24T13:37:43+0000","dateFinished":"2026-06-24T13:37:43+0000","status":"FINISHED","progressUpdateIntervalMs":500,"$$hashKey":"object:15546"},{"text":"%md\n## 2. Data Ingestion & Raw Table Configuration \n\nPrior to executing the ETL pipeline, a Hive **External Table** must be established to map the schema over the raw datasets stored in HDFS.\n\n* **External Schema Mapping**: By utilizing the `EXTERNAL` keyword, Hive registers the dataset metadata within its metastore without mutating or relocating the underlying physical file blocks in HDFS, ensuring data immutability.\n* **Header Shifting**: The table property `skip.header.line.count=1` is explicitly defined to discard the first row (column headers) of the CSV during runtime, preventing data type casting exceptions.","user":"anonymous","dateUpdated":"2026-06-24T14:45:18+0000","config":{"colWidth":12,"enabled":true,"results":{},"editorSetting":{"language":"markdown","editOnDblClick":true},"editorMode":"ace/mode/markdown","editorHide":true},"settings":{"params":{},"forms":{}},"results":{"code":"SUCCESS","msg":[{"type":"HTML","data":"<h2>2. Data Ingestion &amp; Raw Table Configuration</h2>\n<p>Prior to executing the ETL pipeline, a Hive <strong>External Table</strong> must be established to map the schema over the raw datasets stored in HDFS.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>External Schema Mapping</strong>: By utilizing the <code>EXTERNAL</code> keyword, Hive registers the dataset metadata within its metastore without mutating or relocating the underlying physical file blocks in HDFS, ensuring data immutability.</li>\n<li><strong>Header Shifting</strong>: The table property <code>skip.header.line.count=1</code> is explicitly defined to discard the first row (column headers) of the CSV during runtime, preventing data type casting exceptions.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]},"apps":[],"jobName":"paragraph_1782301638007_2073642416","id":"20260624-114718_461036688","dateCreated":"2026-06-24T11:47:18+0000","dateStarted":"2026-06-24T11:55:43+0000","dateFinished":"2026-06-24T11:55:43+0000","status":"FINISHED","progressUpdateIntervalMs":500,"$$hashKey":"object:15547"},{"text":"%jdbc(hive)\r\n\r\nDROP TABLE IF EXISTS default.light_spotify_dataset_raw;\r\n\r\nCREATE EXTERNAL TABLE default.light_spotify_dataset_raw (\r\n    artist STRING,\r\n    song STRING,\r\n    emotion STRING,\r\n    variance FLOAT,\r\n    genre STRING,\r\n    release_date STRING,\r\n    track_key STRING,\r\n    tempo FLOAT,\r\n    loudness FLOAT,\r\n    explicit STRING,\r\n    popularity INT,\r\n    energy INT,\r\n    danceability INT,\r\n    positiveness INT,\r\n    speechiness INT,\r\n    liveness INT,\r\n    acousticness INT,\r\n    instrumentalness INT\r\n)\r\nROW FORMAT DELIMITED\r\nFIELDS TERMINATED BY ','\r\nSTORED AS TEXTFILE\r\nLOCATION '/user/maria_dev/spotify_data/'\r\nTBLPROPERTIES (\"skip.header.line.count\"=\"1\");","user":"anonymous","dateUpdated":"2026-06-24T12:56:26+0000","config":{"colWidth":12,"enabled":true,"results":{},"editorSetting":{"language":"sql","editOnDblClick":false},"editorMode":"ace/mode/sql"},"settings":{"params":{},"forms":{}},"results":{"code":"SUCCESS","msg":[{"type":"TEXT","data":"Query executed successfully. Affected rows : -1"},{"type":"TEXT","data":"Query executed successfully. Affected rows : -1"}]},"apps":[],"jobName":"paragraph_1782301914959_1302603975","id":"20260624-115154_1006326712","dateCreated":"2026-06-24T11:51:54+0000","dateStarted":"2026-06-24T12:56:26+0000","dateFinished":"2026-06-24T12:56:27+0000","status":"FINISHED","progressUpdateIntervalMs":500,"$$hashKey":"object:15548"},{"text":"%jdbc(hive)\r\n\r\n-- Preview the first 10 rows of cleaned data\r\nSELECT artist, song, emotion, genre, release_date, popularity \r\nFROM default.light_spotify_dataset_raw \r\nLIMIT 10;","user":"anonymous","dateUpdated":"2026-06-24T14:45:38+0000","config":{"colWidth":12,"enabled":true,"results":{"0":{"graph":{"mode":"table","height":300,"optionOpen":false},"helium":{}}},"editorSetting":{"language":"sql","editOnDblClick":false},"editorMode":"ace/mode/sql","editorHide":false},"settings":{"params":{},"forms":{}},"results":{"code":"SUCCESS","msg":[{"type":"TABLE","data":"artist\tsong\temotion\tgenre\trelease_date\tpopularity\nABBA\tShe's My Kind Of Girl\tjoy\tpop\t2014\t31\nABBA\t\"Andante\t Andante\"\t0.20222222222222216\tpop\tnull\nABBA\tAs Good As New\tsadness\tpop\t1979\t50\nABBA\tBang\tjoy\tpop\t1975\t52\nABBA\tBang-A-Boomerang\tjoy\tpop\t1975\t52\nABBA\tBurning My Bridges\tanger\tpop\t2013\t34\nABBA\tCassandra\tsadness\tpop\t1981\t39\nABBA\tChiquitita\tsadness\tpop\t1979\t74\nABBA\tCrazy World\tsurprise\tpop\t1975\t39\nABBA\tCrying Over You\tanger\tpop\t2007\t56\n"}]},"apps":[],"jobName":"paragraph_1782302001920_-1592876685","id":"20260624-115321_853840993","dateCreated":"2026-06-24T11:53:21+0000","dateStarted":"2026-06-24T12:56:31+0000","dateFinished":"2026-06-24T12:56:31+0000","status":"FINISHED","progressUpdateIntervalMs":500,"$$hashKey":"object:15549"},{"text":"%md\r\n## 3. Data Cleaning \r\n\r\nInitial data auditing revealed systematic anomalies within the raw dataset, primarily characterized by structural column misalignments—where numerical metrics shifted into categorical text fields—and severe case inconsistencies. To mitigate these infrastructure-level data noises, the ETL pipeline executes four rigorous distributed data transformation policies:\r\n\r\n* **String Normalization and Token Scrubbing**: Invokes the `TRIM()` function to strip extraneous padding, trailing whitespaces, and escape sequences from text variables, thereby guaranteeing categorical integrity.\r\n* **Case Uniformity Harmonization**: Applies `LOWER()` and `UPPER()` functional mappings to standardize the `emotion` and `genre` attributes, eliminating lexical variance and preventing group fragmentation during downstream aggregation phases.\r\n* **Temporal Feature Extraction and Casting**: Utilizes the `SUBSTR()` function to isolate chronological prefixes from raw date strings, subsequently applying a `CAST()` operator to convert them into structured integer components (`release_year`) for time-series dimensionality.\r\n* **Boundary Constraint Validation and Anomaly Filtering**: Establishes a formal validation gatekeeper using `WHERE popularity BETWEEN 0 AND 100` in conjunction with logical non-null constraints. This systematically drops malformed records corrupted by structural column-shifting errors.","user":"anonymous","dateUpdated":"2026-06-24T12:53:27+0000","config":{"colWidth":12,"enabled":true,"results":{},"editorSetting":{"language":"markdown","editOnDblClick":true},"editorMode":"ace/mode/markdown","editorHide":true,"tableHide":false},"settings":{"params":{},"forms":{}},"results":{"code":"SUCCESS","msg":[{"type":"HTML","data":"<h2>3. Data Cleaning</h2>\n<p>Initial data auditing revealed systematic anomalies within the raw dataset, primarily characterized by structural column misalignments—where numerical metrics shifted into categorical text fields—and severe case inconsistencies. To mitigate these infrastructure-level data noises, the ETL pipeline executes four rigorous distributed data transformation policies:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>String Normalization and Token Scrubbing</strong>: Invokes the <code>TRIM()</code> function to strip extraneous padding, trailing whitespaces, and escape sequences from text variables, thereby guaranteeing categorical integrity.</li>\n<li><strong>Case Uniformity Harmonization</strong>: Applies <code>LOWER()</code> and <code>UPPER()</code> functional mappings to standardize the <code>emotion</code> and <code>genre</code> attributes, eliminating lexical variance and preventing group fragmentation during downstream aggregation phases.</li>\n<li><strong>Temporal Feature Extraction and Casting</strong>: Utilizes the <code>SUBSTR()</code> function to isolate chronological prefixes from raw date strings, subsequently applying a <code>CAST()</code> operator to convert them into structured integer components (<code>release_year</code>) for time-series dimensionality.</li>\n<li><strong>Boundary Constraint Validation and Anomaly Filtering</strong>: Establishes a formal validation gatekeeper using <code>WHERE popularity BETWEEN 0 AND 100</code> in conjunction with logical non-null constraints. This systematically drops malformed records corrupted by structural column-shifting errors.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]},"apps":[],"jobName":"paragraph_1782302700876_145000683","id":"20260624-120500_384773057","dateCreated":"2026-06-24T12:05:00+0000","dateStarted":"2026-06-24T12:53:27+0000","dateFinished":"2026-06-24T12:53:27+0000","status":"FINISHED","progressUpdateIntervalMs":500,"$$hashKey":"object:15550"},{"text":"%jdbc(hive)\r\n\r\nDROP TABLE IF EXISTS default.spotify_cleaned;\r\n\r\nCREATE TABLE default.spotify_cleaned AS\r\nSELECT \r\n    TRIM(artist) AS artist,          \r\n    TRIM(song) AS song,              \r\n    LOWER(emotion) AS emotion,       \r\n    variance,\r\n    UPPER(TRIM(genre)) AS genre,           \r\n    CAST(SUBSTR(TRIM(release_date), 1, 4) AS INT) AS release_year, \r\n    track_key,\r\n    tempo,\r\n    loudness,\r\n    popularity\r\nFROM default.light_spotify_dataset_raw\r\nWHERE artist IS NOT NULL AND artist != ''    \r\n  AND song IS NOT NULL AND song != ''        \r\n  AND emotion IS NOT NULL AND emotion != 'Unknown' AND emotion != '' \r\n  AND popularity BETWEEN 0 AND 100           \r\n  AND genre RLIKE '^[a-zA-Z[:space:]\\\\-/]+$'\r\n  AND tempo IS NOT NULL AND tempo > 0\r\nGROUP BY artist, song, emotion, variance, genre, release_date, track_key, tempo, loudness, popularity;","user":"anonymous","dateUpdated":"2026-06-24T12:57:26+0000","config":{"colWidth":12,"enabled":true,"results":{},"editorSetting":{"language":"sql","editOnDblClick":false},"editorMode":"ace/mode/sql"},"settings":{"params":{},"forms":{}},"results":{"code":"SUCCESS","msg":[{"type":"TEXT","data":"Query executed successfully. Affected rows : -1"},{"type":"TEXT","data":"Query executed successfully. Affected rows : -1"}]},"apps":[],"jobName":"paragraph_1782305839087_-869311265","id":"20260624-125719_324918831","dateCreated":"2026-06-24T12:57:19+0000","dateStarted":"2026-06-24T12:57:26+0000","dateFinished":"2026-06-24T12:58:56+0000","status":"FINISHED","progressUpdateIntervalMs":500,"$$hashKey":"object:15551"},{"text":"%jdbc(hive)\r\n\r\n-- Preview the first 10 rows of cleaned data\r\nSELECT artist, song, emotion, genre, release_year, popularity \r\nFROM default.spotify_cleaned \r\nLIMIT 10;","user":"anonymous","dateUpdated":"2026-06-24T12:59:13+0000","config":{"colWidth":12,"enabled":true,"results":{},"editorSetting":{"language":"sql","editOnDblClick":false},"editorMode":"ace/mode/sql"},"settings":{"params":{},"forms":{}},"results":{"code":"SUCCESS","msg":[{"type":"TABLE","data":"artist\tsong\temotion\tgenre\trelease_year\tpopularity\n\"\"\"Macho Man\"\" Randy Savage\"\tBe a Man\tanger\tRAP\t2019\t0\n\"\"\"Weird Al\"\" Yankovic\"\tAlbuquerque\tanger\tCOMEDY\t1999\t40\n\"\"\"Weird Al\"\" Yankovic\"\tAmish Paradise\tjoy\tCOMEDY\t1996\t56\n\"\"\"Weird Al\"\" Yankovic\"\tAngry White Boy Polka\tjoy\tCOMEDY\t2003\t40\n\"\"\"Weird Al\"\" Yankovic\"\tAnother One Rides the Bus\tsadness\tCOMEDY\t2024\t38\n\"\"\"Weird Al\"\" Yankovic\"\tBedrock Anthem\tjoy\tCOMEDY\t1993\t29\n\"\"\"Weird Al\"\" Yankovic\"\tBob\tjoy\tCOMEDY\t2003\t25\n\"\"\"Weird Al\"\" Yankovic\"\tCanadian Idiot\tfear\tCOMEDY\t2006\t44\n\"\"\"Weird Al\"\" Yankovic\"\tChristmas at Ground Zero\tjoy\tCOMEDY\t1986\t27\n\"\"\"Weird Al\"\" Yankovic\"\tClose but No Cigar\tjoy\tCOMEDY\t2006\t37\n"}]},"apps":[],"jobName":"paragraph_1782303295757_-602106704","id":"20260624-121455_121771241","dateCreated":"2026-06-24T12:14:55+0000","dateStarted":"2026-06-24T12:59:13+0000","dateFinished":"2026-06-24T12:59:13+0000","status":"FINISHED","progressUpdateIntervalMs":500,"$$hashKey":"object:15552"},{"text":"%md\r\n# 4. Data Visualizations\r\n\r\nIn this section, we turn our clean data into visual charts using Apache Zeppelin's built-in graphing tools. While running SQL queries gives us precise numbers and tables, looking at rows of text makes it hard to spot big-picture trends. By converting these tables into charts—like bar graphs, line timelines, and scatter plots—we can immediately see which music genres dominate the market, how listener emotions have shifted over the decades, and how different audio features affect a song's popularity. This visualization step helps us easily double-check our data quality and find clear, actionable insights for the music industry.","user":"anonymous","dateUpdated":"2026-06-24T15:15:31+0000","config":{"colWidth":12,"enabled":true,"results":{},"editorSetting":{"language":"markdown","editOnDblClick":true},"editorMode":"ace/mode/markdown","editorHide":true,"tableHide":false},"settings":{"params":{},"forms":{}},"results":{"code":"SUCCESS","msg":[{"type":"HTML","data":"<h1>4. Data Visualizations</h1>\n<p>In this section, we turn our clean data into visual charts using Apache Zeppelin's built-in graphing tools. While running SQL queries gives us precise numbers and tables, looking at rows of text makes it hard to spot big-picture trends. By converting these tables into charts—like bar graphs, line timelines, and scatter plots—we can immediately see which music genres dominate the market, how listener emotions have shifted over the decades, and how different audio features affect a song's popularity. This visualization step helps us easily double-check our data quality and find clear, actionable insights for the music industry.</p>\n"}]},"apps":[],"jobName":"paragraph_1782303494722_2069092183","id":"20260624-121814_86158484","dateCreated":"2026-06-24T12:18:14+0000","dateStarted":"2026-06-24T15:15:31+0000","dateFinished":"2026-06-24T15:15:31+0000","status":"FINISHED","progressUpdateIntervalMs":500,"$$hashKey":"object:15553"},{"text":"%jdbc(hive)\r\n\r\n-- Analytical Scenario 1: Compute track volume, mean popularity, and mean tempo by genre\r\nSELECT \r\n    genre,\r\n    COUNT(1) AS track_volume,\r\n    ROUND(AVG(popularity), 2) AS mean_popularity,\r\n    ROUND(AVG(tempo), 2) AS mean_tempo\r\nFROM default.spotify_cleaned\r\nGROUP BY genre\r\nHAVING track_volume > 10\r\nORDER BY mean_popularity DESC;","user":"anonymous","dateUpdated":"2026-06-24T19:28:22+0000","config":{"colWidth":12,"enabled":true,"results":{"0":{"graph":{"mode":"multiBarChart","height":300,"optionOpen":true,"setting":{"multiBarChart":{"stacked":false},"lineChart":{}},"commonSetting":{},"keys":[{"name":"genre","index":0,"aggr":"sum"}],"groups":[],"values":[{"name":"mean_popularity","index":2,"aggr":"sum"},{"name":"mean_tempo","index":3,"aggr":"sum"}]},"helium":{}}},"editorSetting":{"language":"sql","editOnDblClick":false},"editorMode":"ace/mode/sql"},"settings":{"params":{},"forms":{}},"results":{"code":"SUCCESS","msg":[{"type":"TABLE","data":"genre\ttrack_volume\tmean_popularity\tmean_tempo\nALTERNATIVE\t18934\t42.48\t124.65\nRAP\t32996\t42.07\t121.22\nELECTRONIC\t5127\t41.73\t122.65\nREGGAE\t1951\t41.62\t117.0\nSOUL\t8700\t41.37\t114.74\nMETAL\t10421\t40.52\t126.68\nPOP\t46542\t40.3\t120.64\nSOUNDTRACK\t2570\t38.45\t116.49\nHIP-HOP\t17283\t38.23\t116.03\nROCK\t12818\t37.05\t122.6\nFOLK\t10467\t34.48\t116.77\nPROGRESSIVE\t2997\t33.95\t121.72\nCOMEDY\t1028\t33.89\t122.89\nCHRISTIAN\t2857\t33.65\t121.96\nOPERA\t90\t33.36\t113.18\nWORLD\t306\t32.56\t116.26\nJAZZ\t4064\t31.94\t112.41\nXMAS\t281\t26.46\t122.41\nUNKNOWN\t285\t26.28\t123.6\n"}]},"apps":[],"jobName":"paragraph_1782303747156_-1020689961","id":"20260624-122227_1244431373","dateCreated":"2026-06-24T12:22:27+0000","dateStarted":"2026-06-24T15:15:53+0000","dateFinished":"2026-06-24T15:16:02+0000","status":"FINISHED","progressUpdateIntervalMs":500,"$$hashKey":"object:15554"},{"text":"%md\r\n### 4.1 Popularity and Average Tempo Across Music Genres (Bar Chart)\r\n\r\nThis bar chart provides an overview of how different musical genres perform in terms of popularity and average tempo:\r\n\r\n* **Popularity Trends**: Looking at the darker blue bars (`mean_popularity`), genres such as `ALTERNATIVE`, `RAP`, `ELECTRONIC`, and `REGGAE` lead the chart with stable popularity scores. This pattern indicates that streaming audiences tend to show a clear preference for these rhythm-driven and cross-over genres.\r\n* **Consistency in Tempo**: The light blue bars representing `mean_tempo` (average beats per minute) are remarkably consistent across almost all genres, generally staying around the 110–120 BPM range. This shows that despite differences in musical style or instruments, modern tracks often share a very similar speed to maintain a good rhythmic appeal for listeners.\r\n* **Impact of Data Filtering**: The clear and organized presentation of genres on the X-axis confirms the usefulness of the `HAVING track_volume > 10` filter in the query. By filtering out rare sub-genres or typos with very low track counts, the chart stays clean and focuses only on meaningful market trends.","user":"anonymous","dateUpdated":"2026-06-24T19:54:50+0000","config":{"colWidth":12,"enabled":true,"results":{},"editorSetting":{"language":"markdown","editOnDblClick":true},"editorMode":"ace/mode/markdown","editorHide":true,"tableHide":false},"settings":{"params":{},"forms":{}},"results":{"code":"SUCCESS","msg":[{"type":"HTML","data":"<h3>4.1 Popularity and Average Tempo Across Music Genres (Bar Chart)</h3>\n<p>This bar chart provides an overview of how different musical genres perform in terms of popularity and average tempo:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Popularity Trends</strong>: Looking at the darker blue bars (<code>mean_popularity</code>), genres such as <code>ALTERNATIVE</code>, <code>RAP</code>, <code>ELECTRONIC</code>, and <code>REGGAE</code> lead the chart with stable popularity scores. This pattern indicates that streaming audiences tend to show a clear preference for these rhythm-driven and cross-over genres.</li>\n<li><strong>Consistency in Tempo</strong>: The light blue bars representing <code>mean_tempo</code> (average beats per minute) are remarkably consistent across almost all genres, generally staying around the 110–120 BPM range. This shows that despite differences in musical style or instruments, modern tracks often share a very similar speed to maintain a good rhythmic appeal for listeners.</li>\n<li><strong>Impact of Data Filtering</strong>: The clear and organized presentation of genres on the X-axis confirms the usefulness of the <code>HAVING track_volume &gt; 10</code> filter in the query. By filtering out rare sub-genres or typos with very low track counts, the chart stays clean and focuses only on meaningful market trends.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]},"apps":[],"jobName":"paragraph_1782329690714_-693633956","id":"20260624-193450_14189509","dateCreated":"2026-06-24T19:34:50+0000","dateStarted":"2026-06-24T19:54:50+0000","dateFinished":"2026-06-24T19:54:50+0000","status":"FINISHED","progressUpdateIntervalMs":500,"$$hashKey":"object:15555"},{"text":"%jdbc(hive)\r\n-- Analytical Scenario 2: Track longitudinal trajectory and volume of psychoacoustic emotions from 1970 onwards\r\nSELECT \r\n    release_year,\r\n    emotion,\r\n    COUNT(1) AS annual_track_volume,\r\n    ROUND(AVG(loudness), 2) AS avg_sonic_loudness\r\nFROM default.spotify_cleaned\r\nWHERE release_year IS NOT NULL AND release_year >= 1970\r\nGROUP BY release_year, emotion\r\nORDER BY release_year ASC, annual_track_volume DESC;","user":"anonymous","dateUpdated":"2026-06-24T19:40:40+0000","config":{"colWidth":12,"enabled":true,"results":{"0":{"graph":{"mode":"lineChart","height":300,"optionOpen":true,"setting":{"multiBarChart":{"stacked":true},"lineChart":{}},"commonSetting":{},"keys":[{"name":"release_year","index":0,"aggr":"sum"}],"gro