w and uniform columns for their top 3 songs. This suggests a more decentralized competitive environment where audience attention is distributed across a broader catalog of music rather than being concentrated around a few individual hits.\r\n* **Effectiveness of Query Filtering**: By restricting the data to rows where `intra_genre_rank <= 3`, the query successfully isolates the top-performing songs. This allows for a direct comparison of peak market performance across different musical styles without the distortion of secondary or low-volume data points.","user":"anonymous","dateUpdated":"2026-06-24T19:53:41+0000","config":{"colWidth":12,"enabled":true,"results":{},"editorSetting":{"language":"markdown","editOnDblClick":true},"editorMode":"ace/mode/markdown","editorHide":true,"tableHide":false},"settings":{"params":{},"forms":{}},"results":{"code":"SUCCESS","msg":[{"type":"HTML","data":"<h3>4.3 Intra-Genre Popularity Distribution for Top-3 Tracks (Bar Chart)</h3>\n<p>This chart illustrates the market performance of the top 3 tracks within each musical genre for releases from 2010 onward, filtered using the analytical window function <code>DENSE_RANK()</code>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>High Concentration in Specific Genres</strong>: The visualization shows a clear imbalance in cumulative popularity across different genres. <code>RAP</code> and <code>SOUL</code> display significantly higher columns compared to other categories. This indicates that the leading tracks within these specific genres managed to capture a substantial share of listener engagement and streaming traffic during this period.</li>\n<li><strong>Fragmented Market Dynamics</strong>: In contrast, major genres such as <code>POP</code>, <code>ROCK</code>, and <code>ELECTRONIC</code> exhibit relatively low and uniform columns for their top 3 songs. This suggests a more decentralized competitive environment where audience attention is distributed across a broader catalog of music rather than being concentrated around a few individual hits.</li>\n<li><strong>Effectiveness of Query Filtering</strong>: By restricting the data to rows where <code>intra_genre_rank &lt;= 3</code>, the query successfully isolates the top-performing songs. This allows for a direct comparison of peak market performance across different musical styles without the distortion of secondary or low-volume data points.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]},"apps":[],"jobName":"paragraph_1782330732509_1920833343","id":"20260624-195212_916733495","dateCreated":"2026-06-24T19:52:12+0000","dateStarted":"2026-06-24T19:53:41+0000","dateFinished":"2026-06-24T19:53:41+0000","status":"FINISHED","progressUpdateIntervalMs":500,"$$hashKey":"object:15559"},{"text":"%jdbc(hive)\r\n\r\n-- Analytical Scenario 4: Perform linear correlation and regression analysis between acoustic loudness and market popularity\r\nSELECT \r\n    CAST(loudness AS INT) AS loudness_bucket, \r\n    genre,\r\n    COUNT(1) AS bucket_track_volume,\r\n    ROUND(AVG(popularity), 2) AS avg_popularity\r\nFROM default.spotify_cleaned\r\nWHERE loudness IS NOT NULL\r\nGROUP BY CAST(loudness AS INT), genre\r\nHAVING bucket_track_volume > 5\r\nORDER BY loudness_bucket ASC;","user":"anonymous","dateUpdated":"2026-06-24T15:46:28+0000","config":{"colWidth":12,"enabled":true,"results":{"0":{"graph":{"mode":"scatterChart","height":300,"optionOpen":false,"setting":{"multiBarChart":{"stacked":false},"scatterChart":{"xAxis":{"name":"loudness_bucket","index":0,"aggr":"sum"},"group":{"name":"genre","index":1,"aggr":"sum"},"yAxis":{"name":"avg_popularity","index":3,"aggr":"sum"}}},"keys":[{"name":"loudness_bucket","index":0,"aggr":"sum"}],"groups":[{"name":"genre","index":1,"aggr":"sum"}],"values":[{"name":"avg_popularity","index":3,"aggr":"sum"}]},"helium":{}}},"editorSetting":{"language":"sql","editOnDblClick":false},"editorMode":"ace/mode/sql"},"settings":{"params":{},"forms":{}},"results":{"code":"SUCCESS","msg":[{"type":"TABLE","data":"loudness_bucket\tgenre\tbucket_track_volu